  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Config
    The Config class reads the configuration file and configures the Simulator.
    Event
    The Event class which represents an event to occur in the simulator.
    Link
    A Link class that represents a link between two routers.
    Packet
    The Packet class models a network packet.
    Payload
    The Payload class that represents the payload of a packet.
    Router
    The Router class represents a router.
    RoutingAlgorithm
    The RoutingAlgorithm interface should be implemented by any class whose instances are intended to provide the routing algorithm.
    RoutingPacket
    The RoutingPacket constructor.
    RoutingTableEntry  
    Simulator
    The Simulator class loads the configuration and runs each router with the correct class for that router as specified in the configurtion file.
